The AR usually has a "Master Code" right? This modification itself can cause the game to crash when AR is enabled I imagine. AR I believe hijacks the NMI interrupt or another to do its patching. It is the only way it can rewrite system memory as it's not like it has any direct connection to it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Fri May 20, 2011 9:06 am</p><hr />
